Agreed. Concrete fix: wrap `JSON.parse` in `try/catch` and return a typed result so callers must handle parse failures.

```ts
export function parseInput(raw: string): { ok: true; data: unknown } | { ok: false; error: string } {
  try {
    return { ok: true, data: JSON.parse(raw) }
  } catch (error) {
    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : "Invalid JSON"
    return { ok: false, error: message }
  }
}
```

This avoids uncaught exceptions and makes error handling explicit.

